1.system call of file (argument is file descriptor):
  read, write, creat, open, close, lseek(change read/write starting position),
  unlink(remove file) 

2.error number:
  Usually system call when facing an error will return -1.
  All system calls also leave an error number in an integer variable: errno,
  to specify the error in more detail. A string array sys_errlist gives the 
  readable string explanation of corresponding error number, by sys_errlist[errno].
  e.g.
  #include <errno.h>
  ...
  if(errno > 0 && errno < sys_nerr)
    fprintf(stderr, "%s", sys_errlist[errno]);

3.directory:
  directory is a file to contain pair of file names and inode number.
  e.g. read current directory: open(".", 0).

4.handle signal:
  signal(signal_number, handler_function)
